# Accessibility

Atlas targets WCAG 2.2 AA. Every interactive component must:

1. Have a keyboard-only interaction path that matches the mouse path.
2. Announce state changes to screen readers.
3. Pass axe with no violations at default settings.
4. Support reduced-motion preferences.

## Semantic HTML first

Before reaching for ARIA, use the right element:

- Use `<button>` for anything that triggers an action; never `<div onClick>`
- Use `<a>` for navigation to a URL; never `<button>` with `router.push`
- Use `<label>` associated with form controls via `htmlFor` or nesting
- Use native `<dialog>` where browsers support it; Radix `Dialog` otherwise
- Use `<fieldset>` + `<legend>` for grouped form controls

If ARIA is required, follow the WAI-ARIA Authoring Practices patterns — do not
invent roles.

## Names and descriptions

- Every interactive element has an accessible name (visible label, `aria-label`, or `aria-labelledby`)
- Prefer a visible label over `aria-label` — sighted users deserve labels too
- Icon-only buttons MUST have `aria-label`
- Decorative icons have `aria-hidden="true"`

## Focus

- Focus is always visible. Never `outline: none` without an equivalent `focus-visible` ring
- Focus order matches visual order; do not use positive `tabIndex` values
- When a dialog opens, focus moves to its first focusable element
- When a dialog closes, focus returns to the trigger
- Use `tabIndex={-1}` for programmatically focusable elements not in the tab order

## Keyboard

- Enter + Space activate buttons
- Escape closes modals, popovers, dropdowns
- Arrow keys navigate within composites (menu, tabs, radiogroup)
- Home/End jump to first/last within composites
- Typeahead works in listboxes and menus for lists longer than 10 items

## Announcements

- Form errors use `aria-describedby` pointing at the error text
- Loading/async state announces via a polite live region (use `<LiveRegion>` from `src/components/LiveRegion`)
- Toasts use `role="status"` (polite) for success, `role="alert"` (assertive) for errors

## Color

- Text contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 (≥ 3:1 for large text)
- Never convey information by color alone — pair with icons, text, or patterns
- Focus ring contrast ≥ 3:1 against both adjacent colors

## Motion

- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`: wrap nontrivial transitions in `motion-safe:`
- Do not autoplay video or animation longer than 5 seconds

## Testing

- Every component test renders the component and verifies `getByRole` works with the expected name
- Chromatic runs axe in every story via `@storybook/addon-a11y`
- `pnpm test:a11y` runs Playwright + axe against the built Storybook

## Don't

- Don't use `role="button"` on anything that could be a `<button>`
- Don't use `aria-hidden` on focusable content (it hides from AT but keeps in tab order — a trap)
- Don't trap focus outside of modal contexts
- Don't use `title` as the only source of the accessible name
